node.text: Back in 2017 I posted a Peanuts parody comic as an April Fools Day joke, but I always liked the concept and wanted to make it longer. It only took 4 years but here it is! Read the whole thing on my Patreon for as little as $1! Tap the link on my profile or check my current story! 🎃

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Ellis on July 27, 2021. May be an illustration of text that says '11 നന THANK YOU FOR COMING, GNARLY BROWN. WHY'D YOU MAKE ME GET OUT OF BED, SINUS? WHAT IT YOU WANTED TO SHOW ME? M THIS. @adamtots'.

Photo by Adam Ellis on July 27, 2021. May be a cartoon of text that says 'WHAT... IS IT? THE GIANTGOURD. IT FELL FROM SPACE TONIGHT. IT FILLS ME WITH DREAD. CAN HEAR IT BREATHING, GNARLY. SINUS... THINK WE SHOULD GO. I'M GOING TO STAY AWHILE. YOU GO BACK To BED. I'LL BE FINE. 80'.

Photo by Adam Ellis on July 27, 2021. May be a cartoon of text that says 'BUT SINUS DIDN'T LEAVE. I TOOK FOOD TO HIM A COUPLE TIMES. BUT He DIDN'T TOUCH IT. BROUGHT HIM HIS BLANKET. WORRY ABOUT HIM GETTING COLD.'.
Photo by Adam Ellis on July 27, 2021. May be a cartoon of text.
